verses.text: Praise ye the \+w LORD|strong="H3050"\+w*. Praise, O ye servants of the \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*, praise the name of the \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*.
Blessed be the name of the \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*from this time forth and for evermore.
From the rising of the sun unto the going down of the same the \+w LORDâ€™s|strong="H3068"\+w*name isto be praised.
The \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*ishigh above all nations, andhis glory above the heavens.
Who islike unto the \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*our God, who dwelleth on high,
Who humbleth himselfto behold the things that arein heaven, and in the earth!
He raiseth up the poor out of the dust, andlifteth the needy out of the dunghill;
That he may set himwith princes, evenwith the princes of his people.
He maketh the barren woman to keep house, and to bea joyful mother of children. Praise ye the \+w LORD|strong="H3050"\+w*.
